cards.rules_text:
[i](Inkwells provide I.)[/i]
A deck can have any number of cards named Inkwell.

[i](You may have Masks enter as a ComedyMask or TragedyMask. Swap them at the start of your turn. ComedyMasks provide {C}. TragedyMasks provide {T}.)[/i]
A deck can have any number of cards named Theater Mask.

Transcend Ability: {C}: Puppetear transcends 1. You may trigger the start of turn ability of a ComedyMask.
Transcend Ability: {C}{C}{C}{C}{C}: Puppetear transcends 2.
Attack Ability: {T}: Puppetear attacks 1. You may trigger the start of turn ability of a TragedyMask.
Attack Ability: {T}{T}{T}{T}{T}: Puppetear attacks 2.

As long as there are four or more mediums attached to Roosterror, if another creation you control would deal damage to a creation, it deals that much damage plus 1 instead.
Transcend Ability: {A}I: Roosterror transcends 1.
Attack Ability: {A}I: Roosterror attacks 1.

As a cost to play this card, discard three cards and destroy a creation you control.
Search your deck for any number of Inkwell cards, put them into your play zone, then shuffle. They can't be attached this turn.

Put a Transcendence counter on target creation you control that didn't enter this turn. It can't fully transcend from counters put on it this turn. [i](They still count towards full transcendence later.)[/i]
Destroy target Medium you don't control and target Medium you control.

Transcend Ability: I: As a cost to activate this ability, destroy any number of mediums attached to Consumptoad. Consumptoad transcends 1 for each medium destroyed this way.
Attack Ability: {A}I: Consumptoad attacks 1.

Reactive [i](May be played or activated anytime you have priority.)[/i]
Put a Transcendence counter on target creation you control that's being attacked. It can't fully transcend from counters put on it this turn. [i](They still count towards full transcendence later.)[/i]

Transcend abilities can't put more than one Transcendence counter on a creation.
Transcend Ability: {A}I: Calculaw transcends 1.
Attack Ability: {A}I: Calculaw attacks 1.

As a cost to play this card, put four cards from your reserve into your discard pile.
Draw two cards.

Transcend Ability: {A}I: Squirius transcends 1. Reserve the top card of your deck.
Transcend Ability: {A}{A}II: Squirius transcends 2. Reserve the top card of your deck.
Attack Ability: {A}{A}I: Squirius attacks 1. Put a card from your reserves into your hand.

Play Inksight only if you control two or more Inkwells.
Play Inksight only if you control four or more Mediums.
Draw two cards.

Transcend Ability: {A}{A}II: Put a Transcendence counter on each other creation you control.
Attack Ability: {A}I: Each other creation you control transcends 1.

Ascendant [i](This creation can use a transcend ability the turn it's played.)[/i]
Plausiblade can't fully transcend.
Transcend Ability: {A}I: Put three Transcendence counters on Plausiblade.
Attack Ability: {A}{A}II: Plausiblade attacks X, where X is the number of Transcendence counters on it.

Reactive [i](May be played or activated anytime you have priority.)[/i]
Play Inkseep only if you control two or more Inkwells.
Play Inkseep only if you control four or more Mediums.
Target non-Medium non-Creation card being played is put into its owner's discard pile.
Draw a card.

Reactive [i](May be played or activated anytime you have priority.)[/i]
Up to four target creations can't use attack abilities this turn.

Reactive [i](May be played or activated anytime you have priority.)[/i]
Up to four target creations can't use transcend abilities this turn.

Modifies medium
When Artmorphing enters a play zone, reserve the top card of your deck.
Modified medium is every medium subtype.

Modifies creation
Inky Combativeness provides II to modified creation. Use this I only for attack abilities.

Modifies creation
Inky Vision provides II to modified creation. Use this I only for transcend abilities.

Modifies creation
Inky Balance provides I to modified creation.
Put the top four cards of your deck into your discard pile.

Malore requires 1 more Transcendence counters to fully transcend.
Whenever a tactic you control resolves, if there are five or more Inkwells attached to Malore, put a Transcendence counter on Malore.
At the start of your turn, remove all Transcendence counters from Malore.
Transcend Ability: {A}I: Draw a card.

If you would create one or more tokens, you may create that many plus one of those tokens instead.
Transcend Ability: I: Another creation you control transcends 1.
Create a token that's a copy of target creation you control.

Whenever you destroy a creation you control, at end of turn, if their are three or more mediums attached to Necrestore, create a token that's a copy of the destroyed creation.
Transcend Ability: L: Another token creation you control transcends 2.

Bloodwell provides II instead of I.
As a cost for Bloodwell to provide Ink, destroy a creation you control.

Transcend Ability: {C}{C}: Maskraft transcends 1. You may trigger the start of turn ability of a Tragedy.
Transcend Ability: {C}{C}{C}{C}: Maskraft and another creation you control each transcend 1. Put up to one Mask from your hand into your play zone.

Reactive [i](May be played or activated anytime you have priority.)[/i]
Play Exeunt only if you control a ComedyMask and a TragedyMask.
Return target creation you control and target creation you don't control to their owners' hands.

Whenever one or more Transcendence counters are put on Leadette from an ability of another creation, put a Transcendence counter on Leadette for every third ComedyMask attached to it.
Attack Ability: {T}{T}: Leadette attacks 1.

Act [i](You may play this card with Act. If you do, it gains Aggressive and Ascendant and is returned to your hand at end of turn.)[/i]
Transcend Ability: {C}{C}{C}{C}: Each other creation you control transcends 1.

When Comedeus enters your play zone, trigger the start of turn abilities of each TragedyMask you control.
Transcend Ability: {C}{C}{C}: Comedeus transcends 1, then create a Tragedeus token and move all Transcendence counters from Comedeus to the created token. Destroy Comedeus.

When Comedeus enters your play zone, trigger the start of turn abilities of each TragedyMask you control.
Transcend Ability: {C}{C}{C}: Comedeus transcends 1, then create a Tragedeus token and move all Transcendence counters from Comedeus to the created token. Destroy Comedeus.

When Tragedeus enters your play zone, trigger the start of turn abilities of each ComedyMask you control.
Attack Ability: {T}{T}{T}: Tragedeus attacks 1, then create a Comedeus token and move all Transcendence counters from Tragedeus to the created token. Destroy Tragedeus.

When Tragedeus enters your play zone, trigger the start of turn abilities of each ComedyMask you control.
Attack Ability: {T}{T}{T}: Tragedeus attacks 1, then create a Comedeus token and move all Transcendence counters from Tragedeus to the created token. Destroy Tragedeus.

Used Inkwell provides II instead of I.
At the end of your turn, destroy Used Inkwell if it's attached to a creation.

[i](Swap between ComedyMask and TragedyMask at the start of your turn. ComedyMasks provide {C}. TragedyMasks provide {T}.)[/i]
When Mask of Life enters your play zone, draw a card.

[i](Swap between ComedyMask and TragedyMask at the start of your turn. ComedyMasks provide {C}. TragedyMasks provide {T}.)[/i]
When Mask of Death enters your play zone, draw a card.

[i](MusicNotes provide {N}. As you reserve a MusicNote, you may turn it face up as a composed note.)[/i]
A deck can have any number of cards named Music Note.

Play Bassdrop only if you control four or more mediums.
Put three of your composed notes into your play zone. Destroy them at end of turn.

When Soniclasm enters a play zone, you may trash one of your composed notes. If you do, it gains aggressive. [i](This creation can use an attack ability the turn it's played.)[/i]
Attack Ability: {A}{N}{N}: Soniclasm attacks 2.

As long as there are three or more mediums attached to Symphonor and you have four or more composed notes, transcend abilities you use require 1 less {N}.
Transcend Ability: {A}{N}: Symphonor transcends 1.
Transcend Ability: {A}{A}{A}{A}{N}{N}: Each of your creations transcends 1.

As a cost to play this card, reveal two MusicNote cards from your hand and reserve them.
Draw three cards.

Transcend Ability: {A}{N}{N}: Trash any number of your composed notes. Trebbletrash transcends X, where X is half the number of cards trashed this way, rounded down.
Attack Ability: {N}: Trash any number of your composed notes. Trebbletrash attacks X, where X is half the number of cards trashed this way, rounded down.

As a cost to play this, reserve a MusicNote you control.
Look at the top four cards of your deck. Put one of them into your hand and put the rest on the bottom of your deck in any order.

Reveal the top five cards of your deck. Reserve up to two MusicNote cards from among them and put the rest on the bottom of your deck in a random order. Then if no MusicNote cards were revealed this way, reserve the top card of your deck.

Transcend Ability: {A}{N}: Another creation you control transcends 1.
Transcend Ability: {A}{A}{A}{N}{N}{N}: Another creation you control transcends 1. Draw a card for each of your composed notes.
Attack Ability: {N}: Rhythmaster attacks 1.

[i](Potions provide L. At normal speed, you may destroy three Potions you control to create an Elixir token.)[/i]
A deck can have any number of cards named Potion.
[i](Elixirs provide LL. When an Elixir is used to use a transcend or attack ability, reserve a card from your discard pile.)[/i]

Act [i](You may play this card with Act. If you do, it gains Aggressive and Ascendant and is returned to your hand at end of turn.)[/i]
Transcend Ability: {C}{C}: Another creation you control transcends 1.
Attack Ability: {T}{T}{T}{T}: Knightigrand attacks 2.

Act [i](You may play this card with Act. If you do, it gains Aggressive and Ascendant and is returned to your hand at end of turn.)[/i]
Transcend Ability: {C}{C}{C}{C}: Another creation you control transcends 2.
Attack Ability: {T}{T}: Knightivile attacks 1.

Transcend Ability: {A}L: Impyre transcends 1. Put the top card of your deck into your discard pile.
Transcend Ability: {A}{A}{A}LL: Impyre transcends 2. Put the top three cards of your deck into your discard pile.
Attack Ability: {A}L: Impyre attacks 1. If a creation didn't perish from that attack, reserve a card from your discard pile.
Transcend + Attack Ability: LL: Zombug transcends 1 and attacks 1.
Transcend + Attack Ability: {A}{A}{A}LLL: Lichisect transcends 1 and attacks 1. This turn, whenever you use a transcend + attack ability, copy it.
Transcend + Attack Ability: {A}{A}LL: Ghoulog transcends 1, then attacks X, where X is the number of Transcendence counters on it..

Modifies creation
Alchemic Balance provides L to modified creation.

Modifies creation
Alchemic Combativeness provides LL to modified creation. Use this L only for attack abilities.

Modifies creation
Alchemic Vision provides LL to modified creation. Use this L only for transcend abilities.

Play Reanimate only if you control an Elixir.
As a cost to play this card, discard a card.
Put target creation from your discard pile into your play zone. It transcends 1.
Transcend + Attack Ability: {A}L: Vampyre transcends 1 and attacks 1. Discard a card.
Transcend + Attack Ability: IILL: Sanguink transcends 1 and attacks 1. Draw a card.

Whenever you discard a card, if there are four or more mediums attached to Sanguilord, draw a card.
Transcend + Attack Ability: {A}{A}IILL: Sanguilord transcends X and attacks X, where X is half the number of cards in your hand, rounded down.

Transcend Ability: {A}{A}I: Inkidrain transcends 1. Draw a card.
Transcend Ability: {A}{A}{A}II: Inkidrain transcends 1. Draw a card. Each opponent discards a card.
Attack Ability: {A}{A}I: Inkidrain attacks 1. Each opponent discards a card.

Play Chaos Ritual only if you control an Elixir.
Each player discards two cards. Draw a card.

The first time Songuard would take damage each turn, if you have two or more composed notes, Songuard doesn't take that damage.
Transcend Ability: {A}{N}: Songuard transcends 1.
Transcend Ability: {A}{A}{A}{N}: Songuard transcends 2.
Attack Ability: {A}{A}{N}: Songuard attacks 1. If you have two or more composed notes, Songuard attacks 2 instead.
Reserve a card from your discard pile.

Choose one —
• If you control three or more ComedyMasks, put a Mask from your hand into your play zone as a TragedyMask.
• If you control three or more TragedyMasks, put a Mask from your hand into your play zone as a ComedyMask.

Play Inferno only if you control four or more mediums.
As a cost to play Inferno, return two mediums you control to your hand.
Destroy all creatures.
